{"paragraphs":[{"cues":[{"time":6000,"text":"Space,"},{"time":8000,"text":"we all know what it looks like."},{"time":10000,"text":"We've been surrounded by images of space"},{"time":12000,"text":"our whole lives,"},{"time":14000,"text":"from the speculative images"},{"time":16000,"text":"of science fiction"},{"time":18000,"text":"to the inspirational visions of artists"},{"time":21000,"text":"to the increasingly beautiful pictures"},{"time":24000,"text":"made possible by complex technologies."},{"time":27000,"text":"But whilst we have"},{"time":29000,"text":"an overwhelmingly vivid"},{"time":31000,"text":"visual understanding of space,"},{"time":33000,"text":"we have no sense of what space sounds like."}]},{"cues":[{"time":36000,"text":"And indeed, most people associate space with silence."},{"time":40000,"text":"But the story of how"},{"time":42000,"text":"we came to understand the universe"},{"time":44000,"text":"is just as much a story of listening"},{"time":46000,"text":"as it is by looking."},{"time":49000,"text":"And yet despite this,"},{"time":51000,"text":"hardly any of us have ever heard space."},{"time":54000,"text":"How many of you here"},{"time":56000,"text":"could describe the sound"},{"time":58000,"text":"of a single planet or star?"},{"time":60000,"text":"Well in case you've ever wondered,"},{"time":62000,"text":"this is what the Sun sounds like."}]},{"cues":[{"time":64000,"text":"(Static)"},{"time":78000,"text":"(Crackling)"},{"time":82000,"text":"(Static)"},{"time":88000,"text":"(Crackling)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":92000,"text":"This is the planet Jupiter."}]},{"cues":[{"time":95000,"text":"(Soft crackling)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":115000,"text":"And this is the space probe Cassini"},{"time":118000,"text":"pirouetting through the ice rings of Saturn."}]},{"cues":[{"time":122000,"text":"(Crackling)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":142000,"text":"This is a a highly condensed clump"},{"time":145000,"text":"of neutral matter,"},{"time":147000,"text":"spinning in the distant universe."}]},{"cues":[{"time":151000,"text":"(Tapping)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":169000,"text":"So my artistic practice"},{"time":171000,"text":"is all about listening"},{"time":173000,"text":"to the weird and wonderful noises"},{"time":176000,"text":"emitted by the magnificent celestial objects"},{"time":179000,"text":"that make up our universe."},{"time":182000,"text":"And you may wonder,"},{"time":184000,"text":"how do we know what these sounds are?"},{"time":186000,"text":"How can we tell the difference"},{"time":188000,"text":"between the sound of the Sun"},{"time":190000,"text":"and the sound of a pulsar?"},{"time":192000,"text":"Well the answer"},{"time":194000,"text":"is the science of radio astronomy."},{"time":196000,"text":"Radio astronomers"},{"time":198000,"text":"study radio waves from space"},{"time":200000,"text":"using sensitive antennas and receivers,"},{"time":203000,"text":"which give them precise information"},{"time":205000,"text":"about what an astronomical object is"},{"time":208000,"text":"and where it is in our night sky."},{"time":210000,"text":"And just like the signals"},{"time":212000,"text":"that we send and receive here on Earth,"},{"time":215000,"text":"we can convert these transmissions into sound"},{"time":218000,"text":"using simple analog techniques."},{"time":221000,"text":"And therefore, it's through listening"},{"time":224000,"text":"that we've come to uncover"},{"time":226000,"text":"some of the universe's most important secrets --"},{"time":229000,"text":"its scale, what it's made of"},{"time":232000,"text":"and even how old it is."}]},{"cues":[{"time":234000,"text":"So today, I'm going to tell you a short story"},{"time":237000,"text":"of the history of the universe through listening."},{"time":240000,"text":"It's punctuated"},{"time":242000,"text":"by three quick anecdotes,"},{"time":244000,"text":"which show how accidental encounters"},{"time":246000,"text":"with strange noises"},{"time":248000,"text":"gave us some of the most important information"},{"time":251000,"text":"we have about space."},{"time":253000,"text":"Now this story doesn't start"},{"time":255000,"text":"with vast telescopes"},{"time":257000,"text":"or futuristic spacecraft,"},{"time":260000,"text":"but a rather more humble technology --"},{"time":263000,"text":"and in fact, the very medium"},{"time":265000,"text":"which gave us the telecommunications revolution"},{"time":268000,"text":"that we're all part of today:"},{"time":270000,"text":"the telephone."}]},{"cues":[{"time":272000,"text":"It's 1876, it's in Boston,"},{"time":275000,"text":"and this is Alexander Graham Bell"},{"time":277000,"text":"who was working with Thomas Watson"},{"time":279000,"text":"on the invention of the telephone."},{"time":282000,"text":"A key part of their technical set up"},{"time":285000,"text":"was a half-mile long length of wire,"},{"time":287000,"text":"which was thrown across the rooftops"},{"time":289000,"text":"of several houses in Boston."},{"time":292000,"text":"The line carried the telephone signals"},{"time":295000,"text":"that would later make Bell a household name."},{"time":298000,"text":"But like any long length of charged wire,"},{"time":301000,"text":"it also inadvertently became"},{"time":303000,"text":"an antenna."},{"time":305000,"text":"Thomas Watson"},{"time":307000,"text":"spent hours listening"},{"time":309000,"text":"to the strange crackles and hisses"},{"time":311000,"text":"and chirps and whistles"},{"time":314000,"text":"that his accidental antenna detected."},{"time":317000,"text":"Now you have to remember,"},{"time":319000,"text":"this is 10 years before"},{"time":321000,"text":"Heinrich Hertz proved the existence of radio waves --"},{"time":325000,"text":"15 years before Nikola Tesla's four-tuned circuit --"},{"time":328000,"text":"nearly 20 years before Marconi's first broadcast."},{"time":332000,"text":"So Thomas Watson wasn't listening to us."},{"time":335000,"text":"We didn't have the technology"},{"time":337000,"text":"to transmit."}]},{"cues":[{"time":339000,"text":"So what were these strange noises?"},{"time":343000,"text":"Watson was in fact listening"},{"time":345000,"text":"to very low-frequency radio emissions"},{"time":347000,"text":"caused by nature."},{"time":349000,"text":"Some of the crackles and pops were lightning,"},{"time":352000,"text":"but the eerie whistles"},{"time":355000,"text":"and curiously melodious chirps"},{"time":358000,"text":"had a rather more exotic origin."},{"time":361000,"text":"Using the very first telephone,"},{"time":363000,"text":"Watson was in fact"},{"time":365000,"text":"dialed into the heavens."},{"time":367000,"text":"As he correctly guessed,"},{"time":369000,"text":"some of these sounds were caused"},{"time":371000,"text":"by activity on the surface of the Sun."},{"time":374000,"text":"It was a solar wind"},{"time":376000,"text":"interacting with our ionosphere"},{"time":378000,"text":"that he was listening to --"},{"time":380000,"text":"a phenomena which we can see"},{"time":382000,"text":"at the extreme northern and southern latitudes of our planet"},{"time":385000,"text":"as the aurora."},{"time":387000,"text":"So whilst inventing the technology"},{"time":390000,"text":"that would usher in the telecommunications revolution,"},{"time":394000,"text":"Watson had discovered"},{"time":396000,"text":"that the star at the center of our solar system"},{"time":399000,"text":"emitted powerful radio waves."},{"time":402000,"text":"He had accidentally been the first person"},{"time":405000,"text":"to tune in to them."}]},{"cues":[{"time":407000,"text":"Fast-forward 50 years,"},{"time":409000,"text":"and Bell and Watson's technology"},{"time":412000,"text":"has completely transformed"},{"time":414000,"text":"global communications."},{"time":416000,"text":"But going from slinging some wire"},{"time":418000,"text":"across rooftops in Boston"},{"time":420000,"text":"to laying thousands and thousands of miles of cable"},{"time":423000,"text":"on the Atlantic Ocean seabed"},{"time":425000,"text":"is no easy matter."},{"time":427000,"text":"And so before long,"},{"time":429000,"text":"Bell were looking to new technologies"},{"time":431000,"text":"to optimize their revolution."},{"time":434000,"text":"Radio could carry sound without wires."},{"time":437000,"text":"But the medium is lossy --"},{"time":439000,"text":"it's subject to a lot of noise and interference."},{"time":443000,"text":"So Bell employed an engineer"},{"time":445000,"text":"to study those noises,"},{"time":447000,"text":"to try and find out where they came from,"},{"time":449000,"text":"with a view towards building"},{"time":451000,"text":"the perfect hardware codec, which would get rid of them"},{"time":454000,"text":"so they could think about using radio"},{"time":456000,"text":"for the purposes of telephony."}]},{"cues":[{"time":459000,"text":"Most of the noises"},{"time":461000,"text":"that the engineer, Karl Jansky, investigated"},{"time":464000,"text":"were fairly prosaic in origin."},{"time":466000,"text":"They turned out to be lightning"},{"time":468000,"text":"or sources of electrical power."},{"time":471000,"text":"But there was one persistent noise"},{"time":474000,"text":"that Jansky couldn't identify,"},{"time":476000,"text":"and it seemed to appear"},{"time":478000,"text":"in his radio headset"},{"time":480000,"text":"four minutes earlier each day."},{"time":483000,"text":"Now any astronomer will tell you,"},{"time":485000,"text":"this is the telltale sign"},{"time":487000,"text":"of something that doesn't originate from Earth."},{"time":490000,"text":"Jansky had made a historic discovery,"},{"time":494000,"text":"that celestial objects could emit radio waves"},{"time":497000,"text":"as well as light waves."},{"time":499000,"text":"Fifty years on"},{"time":501000,"text":"from Watson's accidental encounter with the Sun,"},{"time":504000,"text":"Jansky's careful listening"},{"time":506000,"text":"ushered in a new age of space exploration:"},{"time":509000,"text":"the radio astronomy age."},{"time":511000,"text":"Over the next few years,"},{"time":513000,"text":"astronomers connected up their antennas to loudspeakers"},{"time":517000,"text":"and learned about our radio sky,"},{"time":519000,"text":"about Jupiter and the Sun,"},{"time":521000,"text":"by listening."}]},{"cues":[{"time":523000,"text":"Let's jump ahead again."},{"time":525000,"text":"It's 1964,"},{"time":527000,"text":"and we're back at Bell Labs."},{"time":529000,"text":"And once again,"},{"time":531000,"text":"two scientists have got a problem with noise."},{"time":534000,"text":"Arno Penzias and Robert Wilson"},{"time":537000,"text":"were using the horn antenna"},{"time":539000,"text":"at Bell's Holmdel laboratory"},{"time":541000,"text":"to study the Milky Way"},{"time":543000,"text":"with extraordinary precision."},{"time":545000,"text":"They were really listening"},{"time":547000,"text":"to the galaxy in high fidelity."},{"time":549000,"text":"There was a glitch in their soundtrack."},{"time":552000,"text":"A mysterious persistent noise"},{"time":555000,"text":"was disrupting their research."},{"time":557000,"text":"It was in the microwave range,"},{"time":559000,"text":"and it appeared to be coming"},{"time":561000,"text":"from all directions simultaneously."},{"time":563000,"text":"Now this didn't make any sense,"},{"time":565000,"text":"and like any reasonable engineer or scientist,"},{"time":568000,"text":"they assumed that the problem must be the technology itself,"},{"time":571000,"text":"it must be the dish."},{"time":573000,"text":"There were pigeons roosting in the dish."},{"time":576000,"text":"And so perhaps once they cleaned up the pigeon droppings,"},{"time":579000,"text":"get the disk kind of operational again,"},{"time":581000,"text":"normal operations would resume."}]},{"cues":[{"time":584000,"text":"But the noise didn't disappear."},{"time":587000,"text":"The mysterious noise"},{"time":589000,"text":"that Penzias and Wilson were listening to"},{"time":592000,"text":"turned out to be the oldest and most significant sound"},{"time":595000,"text":"that anyone had ever heard."},{"time":597000,"text":"It was cosmic radiation"},{"time":599000,"text":"left over from the very birth of the universe."},{"time":603000,"text":"This was the first experimental evidence"},{"time":606000,"text":"that the Big Bang existed"},{"time":608000,"text":"and the universe was born at a precise moment"},{"time":611000,"text":"some 14.7 billion years ago."},{"time":616000,"text":"So our story ends"},{"time":618000,"text":"at the beginning --"},{"time":620000,"text":"the beginning of all things, the Big Bang."},{"time":623000,"text":"This is the noise that Penzias and Wilson heard --"},{"time":626000,"text":"the oldest sound that you're ever going to hear,"},{"time":629000,"text":"the cosmic microwave background radiation"},{"time":632000,"text":"left over from the Big Bang."}]},{"cues":[{"time":634000,"text":"(Fuzz)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":649000,"text":"Thanks."}]},{"cues":[{"time":651000,"text":"(Applause)"}]}]}